claim.claim-text:
1. A memory package comprising:
a plurality of nonvolatile memory dies;
a plurality of internal communications channels connected to the plurality of nonvolatile memory dies;
a memory controller communicatively connected to the plurality of nonvolatile memory dies by the plurality of internal communications channels; and
a plurality of external interfaces that are coupled to the memory controller and to at least one external communications channel that is connected to a host, wherein the memory controller is further configured to adjust a number of the plurality of external interfaces that are used to access the plurality of nonvolatile memory dies.

10. A memory package, comprising:
a plurality of nonvolatile memory dies;
a plurality of internal communications channels connected to the plurality of nonvolatile memory dies;
a memory controller communicatively connected to the plurality of nonvolatile memory dies by the plurality of internal communications channels;
a plurality of external interfaces that are coupled to the memory controller and to a plurality of external communications channels that are connected to a host; and
a power island that is configured to power each of the plurality of external interfaces on and off.

16. A memory device, comprising:
a plurality of nonvolatile memory dies;
at least one internal communications channel connected to the plurality of nonvolatile memory dies;
a memory controller communicatively connected to the plurality of nonvolatile memory dies by the at least one internal communications channel; and
a plurality of external interfaces that are coupled to the memory controller and to an external communications channel that is connected to a host, wherein the external communications channel branches from a single connection with the host to a plurality of connections with the plurality of external interfaces, and wherein a portion of the plurality of external interfaces are disabled to leave one active external interface that communicates with the host over the external communications channel.
